project.notes: This illustrates the use of a deep learning model called BodyPix. It can detect people in a costume and label which pixels are in which body parts. See https://github.com/tensorflow/tfjs-models/tree/master/body-pix

block-definition.comment: Reports information about people in the image. Can include body part segmentations, poses, and a costume colored by type of body part depending upon the 'options'. See https://ecraft2learn.github.io/ai/AI-Teacher-Guide/chapter-4.html#segmentation

scripts.comment: One thing the muliple person segmenter can do is produce a map of zeroes and ones for each person detected. Here it checks each map for the value under the mouse and if the mouse is over a one at the map location it reports which person has that map.
